metadata.title: Piper PA-28 Cherokee
aws::graph::propositions: Piper PA-28 Cherokee Control Systems and Features
Older Piper PA-28 Cherokee aircraft use an overhead crank for stabilator trim.
The stabilator trim is correctly called an antiservo tab.
Later Piper PA-28 Cherokee aircraft use a trim wheel on the floor between the front seats.
The trim wheel is located immediately behind the flap bar.
All Piper PA-28 Cherokee aircraft have a brake lever under the pilot side of the instrument panel.
Differential toe brakes on the rudder pedals were an optional add-on for earlier Piper PA-28 Cherokee aircraft.
Differential toe brakes became standard with later Piper PA-28 Cherokee models.
Some earlier Piper PA-28 Cherokee aircraft used control knobs for the throttle.
Some earlier Piper PA-28 Cherokee aircraft used control knobs for the mixture.
Some earlier Piper PA-28 Cherokee aircraft used control knobs for the propeller advance where applicable.
Later Piper PA-28 Cherokee aircraft use a collection of two or three control levers in a throttle quadrant.
Piper PA-28 Cherokee aircraft normally include a rudder trim knob.
The rudder trim knob controls a set of springs acting on the rudder pedals rather than an external trim tab on the rudder.
The rudder surface in Piper PA-28 Cherokee aircraft is trimmed by control tension rather than aerodynamically.

text:
Older Cherokees use an overhead crank for stabilator trim (correctly called an antiservo tab), while later ones use a trim wheel on the floor between the front seats, immediately behind the flap bar.
All Cherokees have a brake lever under the pilot side of the instrument panel. Differential toe brakes on the rudder pedals were an optional add-on for earlier Cherokees and became standard with later models.
Some earlier Cherokees used control knobs for the throttle, mixture, and propeller advance (where applicable), while later Cherokees use a collection of two or three control levers in a throttle quadrant.
Cherokees normally include a rudder trim knob, which actually controls a set of springs acting on the rudder pedals rather than an external trim tab on the rudderin other words, the surface is trimmed by control tension rather than aerodynamically.
